items.title: Awesome Mqtt
items.content_text:
### Broker

*   [hrotti (⭐127)](https://github.com/alsm/hrotti) - A MQTT broker written in Go.

### Tools

*   [mqttcli (⭐121)](https://github.com/shirou/mqttcli) - MQTT Client for shell scripting.
*   [MQTTInspector (⭐68)](https://github.com/ckrey/MQTTInspector) - A general MQTT testing app for iOS (iPhone and iPad).
*   [MQTTLens](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/mqttlens/hemojaaeigabkbcookmlgmdigohjobjm) - A Google Chrome application, which connects to a MQTT broker and is able to subscribe and publish to MQTT topics.

### Clients

*   [Machine Head (⭐79)](https://github.com/clojurewerkz/machine_head) - A Clojure MQTT Client.
*   [Moscapsule (⭐276)](https://github.com/flightonary/Moscapsule) - MQTT Client for iOS written in Swift.
*   [mqtt\_cpp (⭐462)](https://github.com/redboltz/mqtt_cpp) - MQTT client for C++14 based on Boost.Asio.
*   [mqtt\_lua](http://geekscape.github.io/mqtt_lua/) - MQTT Client library for the Lua language.
*   [mqtt-client](https://github.com/centamiv/mqtt-client) - A Polymer Web Component that implements a MQTT client (uses Paho mqttws31.js).
*   [MQTT.js](https://github.com/mqttjs) - MQTT client for Node.js.
*   [mqtt (⭐826)](https://github.com/jeffallen/mqtt) - MQTT Clients, Servers and Load Testers in Go.
*   [mqttex (⭐47)](https://github.com/alfert/mqttex) - MQTT implementation in Elixir.
*   [MQTTKit (⭐460)](https://github.com/mobile-web-messaging/MQTTKit) - MQTT Objective-C client for iOS.

### Operating System / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [mqttlauncher (⭐190)](https://github.com/jpmens/mqtt-launcher) - Execute shell commands triggered by published MQTT messages.

### Logging / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [mqttcollect (⭐22)](https://github.com/jpmens/mqttcollect) - A collectd "Exec" plugin for MQTT.

### Smart Home Hardware Interfaces / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [mqtt2homekit (⭐37)](https://github.com/forty2/mqtt2homekit) - Roughly the opposite of [homekit2mqtt (⭐356)](https://github.com/hobbyquaker/homekit2mqtt): Control your HomeKit-enabled devices with MQTT and without Siri or iPhone.

### Smart Home Integration Software / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [Home.Pi (⭐191)](https://github.com/denschu/home.pi) is based on MQTT.

### Home Entertainment / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [kodi2mqtt (⭐84)](https://github.com/owagner/kodi2mqtt) - Interface between a Kodi media center instance and MQTT.
*   [MQTT-DashCast-Docker (⭐5)](https://github.com/mukowman/MQTT-DashCast-Docker) - MQTT Docker to launch DashCast session on Chromecast.

### Misc / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [bt-mqtt-gateway (⭐557)](https://github.com/zewelor/bt-mqtt-gateway) - Easily extensible Bluetooth to MQTT gateway, currently supports: EQ3 smart thermostat, Xiaomi Mi Scale, Linak Desk, MySensors and Xiaomi Mi Flora plant sensor.
*   Tasker (Automation for Android) [MQTT Publisher Plugin](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.nosybore.mqttpublishplugin).

### Visualization, Dashboards / Firmwares for ESP based Devices

*   [node-red-dashboard (⭐1.4k)](https://github.com/node-red/node-red-dashboard) - A dashboard UI for Node-RED.
